Police officers in Mombasa on Monday arrested two terror suspects at the Likoni ferry crossing and recovered weapons including two AK-47 rifles and ammunition. The suspects, who were in a Toyota Probox, were attempting to cross over from the South Coast towards Kisiwani in Mombasa. They were hounded out of the vehicle by at least 10 Anti-Terror Police officers armed to the teeth. The officers covered the suspects’ heads  and then dragged them into their vehicle. Mobile phones, charger, as well as a machete were also recovered from the suspects’ vehicle. Also Read: Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis